00:00:34.800 --> 00:00:37.400
and today I am going
to talk about climate

00:00:37.400 --> 00:00:39.690
change and renewable energy.

00:00:39.690 --> 00:00:42.340
The primary product of
burning of fossil fuels

00:00:42.340 --> 00:00:44.300
is carbon dioxide.

00:00:44.300 --> 00:00:47.820
For centuries, the amount
of carbon dioxide emissions

00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:51.980
in the atmosphere was
300 parts per million.

00:00:51.980 --> 00:00:55.480
But carbon dioxide have
increased dramatically

00:00:55.480 --> 00:00:57.620
and reached an
unprecedented value

00:00:57.620 --> 00:01:00.150
of about 400 parts per million.

00:01:00.150 --> 00:01:02.290
High levels of carbon
dioxide emissions

00:01:02.290 --> 00:01:04.540
are linked to
climate change, which

00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:08.420
has led to increasing
temperatures, melting glaciers,

00:01:08.420 --> 00:01:12.120
rising sea level, changing
rain and snow patterns,

00:01:12.120 --> 00:01:17.580
and also drought, floods,
and other extreme events.

00:01:17.580 --> 00:01:20.150
Climate change is
an important issue,

00:01:20.150 --> 00:01:23.410
and reducing carbon
emission is a challenge.

00:01:23.410 --> 00:01:27.490
In December 2015, world
leaders convened in Paris

00:01:27.490 --> 00:01:30.430
to discuss the reduction of
carbon emissions and climate

00:01:30.430 --> 00:01:33.600
change impacts at a United
