00:03:26.779 --> 00:03:28.570
NOR AISHAH SAIDINA
AMIN: Situated in Johor,

00:03:28.570 --> 00:03:32.210
the most southern state in
peninsula Malaysia, Iskandar,

00:03:32.210 --> 00:03:35.030
Malaysia is a new
development region that

00:03:35.030 --> 00:03:37.620
advocates low carbon emission.

00:03:37.620 --> 00:03:39.950
Most of its carbon
dioxide emission

00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:43.140
are from the electricity
and heating sector.

00:03:43.140 --> 00:03:46.000
As documented in
their low carbon plan.

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:49.030
Iskandar, Malaysia is
projected to be a sustainable

00:03:49.030 --> 00:03:54.470
city by 2025 with only $18.9
million tons of carbon dioxide

00:03:54.470 --> 00:03:59.430
emissions, a 40% reduction
from 2005 levels.

00:03:59.430 --> 00:04:02.280
How can this Iskandar,
Malaysia achieve this target?

00:04:02.280 --> 00:04:05.280
One of the methods
is to utilize waste

00:04:05.280 --> 00:04:09.790
from the oil pump industry to
generate heat and electricity.

00:04:09.790 --> 00:04:13.870
Iskandar, Malaysia is easily
accessible to large areas

00:04:13.870 --> 00:04:16.180
of oil palm plantation.

00:04:16.180 --> 00:04:20.350
The oil pump industry produces
waste such as empty fruit bunch

00:04:20.350 --> 00:04:22.480
and palm oil mill effluent.

00:04:22.480 --> 00:04:26.400
Empty fruit bunch is the residue
you produced when palm fruit is

00:04:26.400 --> 00:04:30.000
taken from a fresh fruit
bunch in the initial process

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:31.900
of a palm oil production.

00:04:31.900 --> 00:04:35.600
Palm oil mill effluent is
the voluminous liquid waste

00:04:35.600 --> 00:04:39.240
that comes from the
sterilization and clarification

00:04:39.240 --> 00:04:42.840
processes in milling oil palm.

00:04:42.840 --> 00:04:46.070
By utilizing waste,
carbon dioxide emissions

00:04:46.070 --> 00:04:49.620
can be significantly
reduced and make the air

00:04:49.620 --> 00:04:52.850
in the region cleaner
and healthier.

00:04:52.850 --> 00:04:55.600
One way to measure
carbon dioxide emissions

00:04:55.600 --> 00:04:58.230
is to use an
integrated model that

00:04:58.230 --> 00:05:02.830
takes into account direct
and indirect carbon dioxide

00:05:02.830 --> 00:05:04.100
emissions.

00:05:04.100 --> 00:05:06.590
The concept of the
model used to probe

00:05:06.590 --> 00:05:10.980
quite a systematic and
comprehensive carbon accounting

00:05:10.980 --> 00:05:13.730
to evaluate carbon
performance, as well

00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:16.260
as to determine the
potential carbon emission

00:05:16.260 --> 00:05:18.754
reduction in the process.

00:05:18.754 --> 00:05:21.820
The model calculates carbon
dioxide emissions from three

00:05:21.820 --> 00:05:25.560
by biomass power plants-- the
bio-xcell plant, Kulim group

00:05:25.560 --> 00:05:28.580
plant, and Ronser biogas plant.

00:05:28.580 --> 00:05:32.230
Initially, carbon accounting
centers for each process

00:05:32.230 --> 00:05:34.900
is divided into smaller units.

00:05:34.900 --> 00:05:38.450
Next, the total monthly
carbon emission equivalent

00:05:38.450 --> 00:05:41.550
is determined, followed by
calculation of the carbon

00:05:41.550 --> 00:05:44.890
dioxide emissions and
carbon emission index

00:05:44.890 --> 00:05:47.710
across the carbon
performance indicators.

00:05:47.710 --> 00:05:50.490
Strategies for reduction
of carbon emissions

00:05:50.490 --> 00:05:52.070
are then implemented.

00:05:52.070 --> 00:05:54.280
The five main
emission contributors

00:05:54.280 --> 00:05:57.860
are identified as carbon
performance indicators.

00:05:57.860 --> 00:06:02.660
These are fuel, water, and
electricity consumption.

00:06:02.660 --> 00:06:06.720
And also waste water and
solid waste generation.

00:06:06.720 --> 00:06:10.030
Empty fruit bunch is
fed into Bio-Xcell Plant

00:06:10.030 --> 00:06:13.990
to generate steam
and electricity.

00:06:13.990 --> 00:06:17.180
Empty fruit bunch is
shredded and then formed

00:06:17.180 --> 00:06:19.490
as solid pellets.

00:06:19.490 --> 00:06:22.510
The pellets are used as
fuels for the boilers

00:06:22.510 --> 00:06:23.990
to produce steam.

00:06:23.990 --> 00:06:28.100
The steam turbine then
generates electricity.

00:06:28.100 --> 00:06:32.010
Meanwhile, Kulim and Ronser
utilize palm oil mill effluent.

00:06:32.010 --> 00:06:35.850
The effluent is retained
in an anaerobic digester

00:06:35.850 --> 00:06:37.580
to produce bio gas.

00:06:37.580 --> 00:06:41.480
The gas runs the turbine
to generate electricity.

00:06:41.480 --> 00:06:43.650
The total monthly
carbon dioxide emissions

00:06:43.650 --> 00:06:45.920
before and after
the implementation

00:06:45.920 --> 00:06:50.040
of the reductions strategies
are exhibited in figure one,

00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:54.660
showing a 27% emissions
reduction at Bio-Xcell,

00:06:54.660 --> 00:06:59.920
15% at Kulim, and 41% at Ronser.

00:06:59.920 --> 00:07:02.750
Figure two compares the
carbon emission index

00:07:02.750 --> 00:07:06.170
after implementing the
reduction strategies.

00:07:06.170 --> 00:07:08.940
In general, all
performance indicators

00:07:08.940 --> 00:07:12.450
show reduced emissions
after innovative strategies

00:07:12.450 --> 00:07:14.020
are implemented.

00:07:14.020 --> 00:07:16.520
In Bio-Xcell, the
carbon emission index

00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:21.110
for fuel and water consumption
decreased significantly

00:07:21.110 --> 00:07:25.540
after solid, empty fruit bunches
replaced the shredded ones.

00:07:25.540 --> 00:07:28.345
In addition, a reduction
of solid waste generation

00:07:28.345 --> 00:07:31.550
in runs of bio gas
was also registered

00:07:31.550 --> 00:07:35.070
after water from the
effluent is recycled.

00:07:35.070 --> 00:07:37.910
Carbon dioxide emissions
can be easily predicted

00:07:37.910 --> 00:07:39.790
using the income model.

00:07:39.790 --> 00:07:42.930
A power plant that utilizes
biomass contributes

00:07:42.930 --> 00:07:46.470
